cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SE 

This paper discusses a method of exfiltrating data from air-gapped computers using power lines, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also involves signal processing and communication theory (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of implementing and evaluating the attack and defensive countermeasures.
